data.chText: 牧场，大农场（尤指北美或澳大利亚的）
data.enText: a large farm, especially in N America or Australia, where cows, horses, sheep, etc. are bred
ranch hands (= the people who work on a ranch )

means: 牧场，大农场(尤指北美或澳大利亚的)

tr: farm consisting of a large tract of land along with facilities needed to raise livestock (especially cattle)

example: Her husband is ranching in Arizona

value.def: A ranch is a large farm used for raising animals, especially cattle, horses, or sheep.

example.ex: He lives on a cattle ranch in Australia.
example.tran: 他在澳大利亚靠一个牧牛场为生。

value.tran: （尤指饲养牛、马、羊等的）大农场，大牧场

trans: 农场庄园；牧场住宅；平房住宅(矮屋顶单层，开敞长方形)
